==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whit
<hw>Whit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wight</ets>,
<ets>wiht</ets>, AS. <ets>wiht</ets> a creature, a thing. See
<er>Wight</er>, and cf. <er>Aught</er>, <er>Naught</er>.]</ety> <def>The
smallest part or particle imaginable; a bit; a jot; an iota; --
generally used in an adverbial phrase in a negative sentence.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Samuel told him every <xex>whit</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>1 Sam. iii.
18.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Every <xex>whit</xex> as great.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So shall I no <qex>whit</qex> be behind in duty.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It does not me a <qex>whit</qex> displease.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>White</ent>⟦br⟧
